# src/styles/ Directory Rules

## Do Not Manually Edit These Files

- **intuit.css** — Synced from the DDMS CDN via `npm run sync-tokens`. Contains all IDS design token CSS custom properties. Run `npm run sync-tokens [version]` to update.
- **index.css** — Global styles. Should not need modification during prototyping.
- **fonts.css** — Font imports. Should not need modification during prototyping.

## Editable Files

- **App.module.css** — Shell-level styles only (minimal). Do not put page-specific styles here.
- **[Name].module.css** — Per-page styles (e.g. `HomePage.module.css`, `SettingsPage.module.css`). Each page has its own CSS Module file. This is where all page-specific styling goes. Uses CSS Modules (Vite auto-scopes `.module.css` files) and design tokens.

## Adding a New Page's Stylesheet

When a skill creates a new page, it also creates a matching `src/styles/[Name].module.css` file. The page component imports it with:

```tsx
import styles from '../styles/[Name].module.css'
```

